        "### Data Analysis Key Findings\n",
        "*   The Excel file `/content/Abbreviations Dictionary R.3.9.5.xlsx` was successfully loaded into a pandas DataFrame and converted into a JSON file named `data.json`. The conversion used `orient='records'`, `force_ascii=False` for proper character handling, and `indent=4` for readability.\n",
        "*   A Streamlit web application (`app.py`) was created and subsequently updated to display the JSON data.\n",
        "*   The `app.py` incorporates a responsive UI using `st.sidebar` and `st.columns`, making it adaptable for various screen sizes.\n",
        "*   Custom CSS was embedded to achieve a Cupertino-like design, including a modern font, an Apple-inspired color palette, rounded corners for UI elements, and subtle shadows for data display components.\n",
        "*   The `data.json` file is loaded within the Streamlit app, with a preview of the first 5 entries shown in one column and the full dataset available via an `st.expander` for organized display.\n",
